Apparently this is the traditional Bulgarian garden order, in a way imitating Eden:

- An apple tree in the centre of the yard
- A pear tree next to the house, used to hang stuff on (bags, sacks, tools)
- Boxtrees along the path, trimmed heavily
- Big walnut tree in the corner
This is true @gaitanalyst

A dogwood tree (mostly used for ritual purposes) is somewhere in the garden, unspecified. A basswood tree is in front of the property (like on the street, not near the house building itself). A water well is always put in front of the house too. Under the walnut, a table is put.

Oaks and other fruitless trees are not planted, they are for the forest. Cherries, plums, and many others are not specified and their position and presence do not carry meaning.
